<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This new variety differs from the other varieties (
<taxonomicName authority="Jacq. var. monogyna" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Crataegus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Crataegus monogyna var. monogyna" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="monogyna" variety="monogyna">Crataegus monogyna Jacq. var. monogyna</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. I. Chr" authorityYear="1992" baseAuthorityName="Lange" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Crataegus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Crataegus monogyna var. lasiocarpa" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="monogyna" variety="lasiocarpa">Crataegus monogyna var. lasiocarpa</taxonomicName>
(Lange) K.I.Christ.) sensu 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/25027810" author="Christensen, KI" journalOrPublisher="Plant Systematics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B3" refString="Christensen, KI, 1992. Revision of Crataegussect.Crataegus and nothosect. Crataeguineae (Rosaceae-Maloideae) in the Old World. Systematic Botany Monographs: 35. https://doi.org/10.2307/25027810" title="Revision of Crataegussect. Crataegus and nothosect. Crataeguineae (Rosaceae-Maloideae) in the Old World. Systematic Botany Monographs: 35." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/25027810" year="1992">Christensen (1992)</bibRefCitation>
by its orange fruit colour in contrast to red fruits in the former.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
